    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="424"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.20 Missions/17</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-23">June 23,
                        1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Chief of the U.S. Military
                    Mission to Iran, General Ridley, has submitted a report on his Mission and has
                    recommended that the Mission be recalled. A copy of this report and
                    recommendation are attached hereto.<note n="12" xml:id="d424fn12">Neither
                        printed.</note> The War Department agrees with General Ridley that there
                    exists no military necessity for this Mission and that virtually its entire
                    usefulness to Iran has already been accomplished. It is felt that the Mission
                    should be withdrawn <pb facs="0425" n="413" xml:id="pg_413"/> whether or not the
                    Iranian Government agrees. However, the Military Mission to Iran originally was
                    dispatched because of State Department considerations and no action leading to
                    its withdrawal will be taken without your agreement. Will you kindly inform the
                    War Department of your views on this matter.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry L. Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
